We are excited to offer you this new opportunity within Wipro Technologies, one of the biggest brands in the industry at this moment with a well-established history in various domains.

As part of this project, your role as an Master Data Analyst will be to build and co-manage a strong relationship with our client organization and perform based on defined SLA and KPIs.










The skills & experience you need:

Previous experience -1 year in Procurement or Order Management - Master data domain
Understanding of Procurement & Supply chain activities
Experience using ERP systems – SAP
Vendor/customer creation/change in SAP
Item/Material creation/change in SAP
MS Excel – advanced user
Highly Quality focused with excellent attention to detail
Ability to work on detailed repetitive tasks
Methodical with a process-oriented approach to work
Excellent customer service / communication skills
Self-motivating and able to prioritize own workload
Team player with a pro-active approach to work and an open and enquiring mind













What you'll be doing:

Standard Costs for all valuated material types (Raw, Pack, Semi-finished and Finished Goods)
Distribution Standard Cost Rates defined by Customer and Product Group (PIB)
Transfer Price Calculation for Intercompany Sales / Transfers provided to the Customer Systems team for loading into SAP.
Activity Rates for Marginal Production, Fixed Production and Distribution.
Following agreed policies, standards and procedures whilst achieving agreed SLA’s.
Responsible for keeping standards and procedural documentation up to date and relevant.
Responsible for performing regular housekeeping activity and producing Master Data quality KPI reporting for Costing related Master data.
With guidance from Master data manager undertake problem solving and route cause analysis activity.
Undertake detailed master data analysis activity as directed by Master Data Manager.










Benefits for working with us:

The chance to work for Top Employer 2024!
Competitive salary with attractive set of social benefits:
Private Pension Plan;
Monthly Benefit budget;
Medical insurance;
Life insurance;
Christmas bonus;
Childbirth allowance;
Relocation package for candidates outside of TIMIS county;
Great career opportunity to work for one of the biggest brands in the world in a unique work environment;
Personal development in a multinational working environment through nice extracurricular activities with the team;
Platform to actively participate and make an impact through Sustainability and Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) projects;
Professional development through a variety of training programs (hard/soft skills);
Extra annual leave days depending on tenure within Wipro;
BOOKSTER opportunities;
Nice designed and central business office;
Coffee and tea on the house + massage at the office;
The promise of an enjoyable first impression after discussing with any of our recruitment colleagues.

